ed Kingdom","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11. februar 1479–Afdød","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Afdød","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11. februar 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11 februari 1479–Overleden","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Overleden","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11 februari 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11 February 1479–Deceased","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Deceased","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11 February 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hunter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: occupational name from Middle English <i>hunter(e)</i> ‘huntsman’ (see   Hunt  ).","Irish (Antrim and Derry): adopted for Gaelic <b>Ó Fiaich</b> (see   Fee  ) due to confusion with the word <i>fiadhach</i> ‘hunt’.","History: A Scottish family of this name (see 1 above) has been established at Hunterston (Ayrshire) since the 13th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Hunt","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a hunter, from Middle English <i>hunte</i> ‘hunter, huntsman’ (Old English <i>hunta</i>). The term was used not only of the hunting on horseback of game such as stags and wild boars, which in the Middle Ages was a pursuit restricted to the ranks of the nobility, but also to much humbler forms of pursuit such as bird catching and poaching for food. The word seems also to have been used as an Old English personal name and to have survived into the Middle Ages as an occasional personal name. Compare   Huntington   and   Huntley  .","Irish: adopted for various Irish surnames containing or thought to contain the Gaelic element <i>fiadhach</i> ‘hunt’; for example <b>Ó Fiaich</b> (see   Fee  ) and <b>Ó Fiachna</b> (see   Fenton  ).","Possibly an Americanized form of German   Hundt  ."]},{"name":"Huntress","meanings":["Scottish: apparently from the feminine form of   Hunter  ."]}]},{"name":"Cuthbert(son)","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: patronymic from the personal name <i>Cudbert</i> (see   Cuthbert  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Cuthbert","meanings":["From an Old English personal name composed of <i>cūð</i> ‘known’ + <i>beorht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was borne by two pre-Conquest English saints: a 7th-century bishop of Lindisfarne and an 8th-century archbishop of Canterbury who corresponded with  St Boniface . The name has been in more or less continuous use in the northern counties of England from the 13th century, though its use has declined over recent decades."]}]},{"name":"Augustus","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name, from the adjective <i>augustus</i> ‘great, magnificent’ (from <i>augere</i> ‘to increase’). This word was adopted as a title by the Roman emperors, starting with Octavian (Gaius Julius Caesar Octavianus), the adopted son of  Julius Caesar , who assumed it in  27  bc   and is now generally known as the  Emperor Augustus . This name, together with   Augusta  , was revived in England in the 18th century, but it has now again declined in popularity."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Cuthbert(son) Augustus Hunter (3) was born on 11 February 1479, in Monmouth, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Loretta Jane Hunter. He died in Earsdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11. veebruar 1479–Surnud","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Surnud","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11. veebruar 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11. helmikuuta 1479–Kuollut","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Kuollut","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11. helmikuuta 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"11 Feb 1479–":"11 février 1479–Décédé","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1518–1586":"1518–1586","1479–Male":"1479–Décédé","1479":"1479","1586":"1586","1540":"1540","1518":"1518","1480":"1480","11 Feb 1479":"11 février 1479","Earsdon, Northumberland, England":"Earsdon, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Monmouth, England":"Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Cuthbert(son) Augustus Hunter (3) est né le 11 février 1479, à Monmouth, Gloucestershire, Angleter